# LHP local caches/state must never be tracked, in ANY project location. The parse cache and
# the persistent graph cache both write to <project_root>/.lhp/cache/; the webapp writes
# .lhp/webapp.db, logs and state. Ignoring .lhp/ globally prevents these from polluting the
# repo (e.g. the e2e fixture testing_project when a webapp test analyzes it in place).
.lhp/
.lhp_state.json
